column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Cloudy , Light Rain , Moderate Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: Water bank to bank and into willows a bit on LB, but not yet into willows on RB. ~.3-.45m before water over bank at gauge on LB. D/S mid channel island not submerged.
column14: Possibly 1st ADCP mmnt at site, GPS data better than BT due missing data due with BT due to turbulence in one section. River at mmnt section appeared reasonably laminar and flat but one area of the river gave BT data problems, tried a number of different cross sections but there was always missing data in one area of the River. No Missing Data with GPS. RR may handle turbulence better but would probably not measure over 50% due to shallow water.   Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of -0.001 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 29.624 River relatively laminar and flat at this stage, Ocassional drifting debris. Levels done in area of BM 4. At this level ~30-45cm before water over bank at gauge. ADCP by Moving Boat

Levels hole chipped mid channel ~ 12m from shore. 10cm snow on ice at gauge, ~50cm snow in forest. Surveyed HW freezeup mark, 29.256m fair-poor ice ledge near shore.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Section control at this stage
column14: Did 1st mmnt 15m d/s of cableway where bank isn't undercut on R/S, got 6.43cms, which plotted +16%, did 2nd mmnt right under cableway and got 5.89cm, which is similar shift to last month's mmnt.  There may have been some errors with depths in the 1st mmnt. Levels were also re-run to confirm there was no error with levels that was making the 1st mmnt plot far to the right. Moved orifice end to deeper water ~2/3 of the way across the channel infront of gauge. Orifice end now in .52m of water at this stage. Algea growth on most rocks on both sides of channel, mid channel showed signes of cobbles and sand movement. Added 1.5 sections of 1.2m steel rod to BM that was started at last visit. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind

The 2nd one is 2m W of BM 1 near the river bank, 19.8m of steel rods driven in, ran out of rods so not driven to refusal, will have to return w/ a few more rods to complete it. Mid-section
